# Verified Research

Chapter data drives what learners read as fact. A prior audit found ~70% of
scholarly "quotes" were fabricated wording attributed to real scholars. These
rules stop that.

## Prime rule

Never write wording in a `quote` or `directQuote` field that you have not seen
with your own eyes in the actual source (WebFetch of the real text, Google Books
snippet, archive.org page). If you did not see it, it is a **summary** — write it
attributively ("Knight argues that…"), never in the author's voice, never in
quote marks. The UI shows quotation marks ONLY for `quoteType: 'verbatim'`.

## Verification ladder → sets `quoteType`

- **verbatim** — Fetched full text from a public-domain repo (perseus.tufts.edu,
  newadvent.org, gutenberg.org, archive.org, ccel.org, egwwritings.org) and copied
  it exactly. Needs `sourceUrl` + `verifyNote` naming edition and page.
- **paraphrase** — Passage found but condensed/modernized. `sourceUrl` + `verifyNote`.
- **summary** — Work is real but exact wording unseen. Reword attributively; best
  `sourceUrl` (publisher / Google Books / Google Scholar) + `verifyNote:
  "Companion summary — not a quotation."`
- **not found** — Source can't be confirmed to exist → DO NOT include the entry.

Never introduce `quoteType: 'unverified'` in new content. If you can't reach at
least summary, remove the entry — do not ship it as unverified.

## Bibliographic rules

Verify author, exact title, publisher, and year before citing (the audit found
wrong years and nonexistent titles for real scholars). Ellen White quotes must be
checked on egwwritings.org and carry the book/page in `reference`.

## Entry shapes (match src/types.ts)

```ts
// historicalSources[]
{ title, author, publication, quote, relevance?,
  quoteType: 'verbatim' | 'paraphrase' | 'summary',
  sourceUrl, verifyNote }

// scholarlyReferences[]
{ author, year, title, source, relevance,
  directQuote,                                  // attributive if not verbatim
  quoteType: 'verbatim' | 'paraphrase' | 'summary',
  sourceUrl, verifyNote }
```

## Checklist before finishing

1. Every new entry has a `quoteType`.
2. No quotation-voice wording under `summary`/`paraphrase`.
3. No new `quoteType: 'unverified'`.
4. `npx tsc --noEmit` passes.
5. Grep the file for `quote:`/`directQuote:` and confirm each has a `quoteType`
   nearby; delete anything you could not verify.
